PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774455107
OL,3,CFM still has 'fight in her', says
OL,4,CLabour candidate, despite poll result
OL,6,FPlaid Cymru's Sioned Williams said the
OL,7,Fpoll "shows us on track to form the
OL,8,FWelsh Government. Of course, it's a
OL,9,Fpoll, and we're not taking anything
OL,10,Ffor granted.
OL,12,F"I think it shows, as well, a
OL,13,Fsubstantial enough gap that we would
OL,14,Fbe able to govern alone, which would
OL,15,Fbe our preference, and also, there
OL,16,Fwould be a progressive majority with
OL,17,Fwhom we could be able to perhaps come
OL,18,Fto an agreement on some policies in
OL,19,Forder to be able to get them as a
OL,20,Fminority government."
OL,26,@oD@FOUtD@AOU|D@UO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/11
